1 1 Hemp;Prohibitions. AmendRSA439-A:4toreadasfollows:
2 439-A:4 Hemp-DerivedProductsContainingTHCProhibited.
3 I. Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to authorize the sale of products that are
4 derived from hemp which contain natural or synthetic tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) greater than 0.3
5 percentonadryweightbasis,whichappearinanyformulation,includingdelta-8THC,delta-9THC,
6 oranyotherTHCisomervariant. Suchproductsareprohibited.
7 II. No person under the age of 21 may purchase, possess, or consume a product
8 derived from hemp which contain natural or synthetic tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) in any
9 amount, which appear in any formulation, including delta-8 THC, delta-9 THC, or any
10 otherTHCisomervariant.
11 III. Any person who knowingly possesses a product in violation of paragraphs I or
12 II shall be guilty of a violation for a first offense and a class B misdemeanor for any
13 subsequentoffense.
14 IV. AnypersonwhoisconvictedofviolatingparagraphIshallbesubjecttoafineof
15 $100 for a first offense, and any subsequent violations shall be guilty of a class B
16 misdemeanor with not less than a $300 fine and not more than a $1,200 fine. The offender
17 shallforfeitthehemp-derivedproducttothestate.
18 V. A corporation or unincorporated association shall be subject to a fine not to
19 exceed $20,000 for a misdemeanor and $1,000 for a violation. A writ of execution may be
20 issued by the court against the corporation or unincorporated association to compel
21 paymentofthefine,togetherwithcostsandinterest.
